{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Create canonical AGENTS.md (rebar dev guide) + reduce CLAUDE.md to a thin @AGENTS.md pointer\n\n## Why\n\n`AGENTS.md` is read natively by Codex, Cursor, Copilot's coding agent, Zed, Windsurf, Amp,\nFactory, Jules, Devin, RooCode, and Cline â€” so a single canonical `AGENTS.md` covers the\necosystem in one move, and Claude Code is bridged by a one-line import. This also fixes the\nsize/duplication anti-pattern: the sections that duplicate `docs/` become one-line pointers.\n\n## What\n\nAuthor a lean `AGENTS.md` at the repo root (target â‰¤ ~200 lines) that keeps rebar-INTERNAL\ndev specifics inline â€” Gerrit split-remote workflow, module-size policy, Serena navigation,\nlocal-dev-env, worktree/venv discipline, CI-before-close, signing â€” and replaces every section\nthat has an authoritative doc with a one-line `docs/â€¦md` pointer (gate protocols â†’\n`docs/plan-review-gate.md`; MCP tool set â†’ `docs/mcp-reference.md`; quality gates + ticket\ntemplate + project criteria â†’ `docs/plan-review-criteria-guide.md`; store-shares-writes â†’\n`docs/concurrency.md`; the native topics â†’ the docs created in the re-home story). Then reduce\n`CLAUDE.md` to a `@AGENTS.md` import line plus only genuinely Claude-only notes (if any). Use\nthe mechanism proven by the import spike (fall back to a symlink only if the spike said so).\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: new `AGENTS.md`, rewritten `CLAUDE.md`. Out: `CLAUDE.local.md` (its own story), the\n`.codex`/`.agents` shims and reference sweep (later story), and any code change.\nDepends on: the import spike (mechanism) and the re-home story (docs homes must exist first).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `AGENTS.md` exists at repo root, â‰¤ ~200 lines, and no section restates a doc that has an\n  authoritative version â€” each such topic is a one-line pointer.\n  - Proving: `wc -l AGENTS.md` â‰¤ 200; reviewer confirms pointer-not-duplicate per topic.\n- [ ] rebar-internal dev specifics (Gerrit, module-size, Serena, local-dev-env, worktree/venv,\n  CI-before-close, signing) are present in `AGENTS.md`.\n  - Proving: `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena|worktree' AGENTS.md` > 0 for each.\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` contains exactly one `@AGENTS.md` import and no duplicated project guidance.\n  - Proving: `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` == 1; `wc -l CLAUDE.md` is small (â‰¤ ~30).\n- [ ] `make lint` passes.\n\n## De-risking results (mechanism proven + size model + Gerrit-condense decision)\n\n- **Mechanism PROVEN** (see S0 / `eastbound-bald-raptors`): `CLAUDE.md` = `@AGENTS.md` + an\n  optional `## Claude Code` section (Anthropic's documented pattern). No symlink.\n- **Imports do NOT save context** (docs: imported files \"load at launch\"). The size win is\n  de-dup into `docs/`, so **AGENTS.md itself must be lean.**\n- **Grounded size model: ~152 lines is achievable at â‰¤200 â€” but ONLY if the Git/Gerrit section\n  is CONDENSED to ~50 lines with the full recipe delegated to `CONTRIBUTING.md`.** CLAUDE.md's\n  Gerrit block is ~126 lines; left verbatim, AGENTS.md would be ~215-230 and MISS â‰¤200.\n  CLAUDE.md already says \"the full contributor guide is CONTRIBUTING.md,\" so condensing loses\n  nothing recoverable. **DECISION: condense Gerrit to agent-actionable rules only** (split\n  remotes `origin`=GitHub+tickets / `gerrit`=review; fresh worktree+venv; `rebar-ticket:`\n  trailer; DCO `Signed-off-by:` line; two-vote gate; self-Submit; feature-branch for multi-story)\n  **+ a pointer to CONTRIBUTING.md.**\n- **INLINE** (kept in full): intro; core operating rule; parallel-agent loop; env bootstrap\n  (`make install`/`make hooks`); module-size policy; Serena nav; condensed Gerrit; 6-line\n  library snippet. **POINTER**: ticket-modelâ†’`docs/ticket-model.md`; session-logsâ†’event-schema\n  + user-guide; cascadeâ†’concurrency I4a; gate protocolsâ†’plan-review-gate.md;\n  quality+template+project-criteriaâ†’plan-review-criteria-guide.md; MCPâ†’mcp-reference.md;\n  store-writesâ†’concurrency.md; libraryâ†’reuse-surface.md.\n- **Two stowaways** wedged under CLAUDE.md's \"Session logs\" heading must be RE-HOMED, not merely\n  relocated: the LLM-agent-operations paragraph â†’ `docs/llm-framework.md`; the\n  completion-verification close-gate blockquote â†’ `docs/plan-review-gate.md`.\n\nRevised Acceptance Criteria (supersede/refine the ones above):\n- [ ] `wc -l AGENTS.md` â‰¤ 200 (target ~150-170); the Git/Gerrit section is â‰¤ ~55 lines and\n  defers the full recipe to CONTRIBUTING.md.\n- [ ] Every topic that has an authoritative doc is a one-line pointer (not a restated section);\n  the two stowaways are re-homed to llm-framework.md / plan-review-gate.md.\n- [ ] `CLAUDE.md` = one `@AGENTS.md` import + optional `## Claude Code` section only.\n  - Proving: `rg -c '@AGENTS.md' CLAUDE.md` == 1; `wc -l CLAUDE.md` â‰¤ ~30.\n- [ ] `make lint` passes."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784232646830009001,"uuid":"b5390584-64f6-4847-98cc-df1a23ada60c"}